   - Acceleration time = sqrt(2 * distance / acceleration) = sqrt(2 * 100 meters / 1 m/s^2) = sqrt(200) = 14.14 seconds.
   - Deceleration time = 14.14 seconds (same as acceleration time).
   - Total stop time = 2 * (14.14 seconds + 14.14 seconds) = 56.56 seconds.

5. **Calculate the total time:**
   - Total time = Time for first person + Total stop time = 40 seconds + 56.56 seconds = 96.56 seconds.

